# EasyHealth API Routes

## x402 paywall pattern

```typescript
// 1. x402 middleware validates payment OR returns 402
// 2. Resolve profile from session/wallet
// 3. Execute business logic
// 4. Record payment_receipts row
```

- Use existing x402 middleware from starter; configure Arc Network seller wallet
- Return 402 before any expensive LLM or storage work on unpaid requests

## Extraction schema (Zod)

```typescript
{
  lab_name: string | null,
  observed_at: string | null, // ISO date
  biomarkers: Array<{
    key: string,      // snake_case e.g. "hba1c"
    name: string,
    value: number,
    unit: string,
    ref_low: number | null,
    ref_high: number | null,
  }>
}
```

Single `generateObject` / structured output call per document - no multi-step pipeline.

## Doctor summary response shape

```typescript
{
  overview: string,
  key_findings: string[],
  changes: string[],
  questions_for_clinician: string[],
  when_to_seek_care: string,
  disclaimer: "This is not medical advice. Consult a healthcare professional."
}
```

## Error handling

- 400: no biomarkers / no observations for summary
- 402: missing x402 payment
- 401: unauthenticated
- 500: extraction failure - set document status `failed`, log error server-side only
